cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for diabetic retinopathy detection using convolutional neural networks (CNN) and regression activation maps (RAM) for visual interpretation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of RAM for visual interpretation could also place the paper in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
